
@startuml
class City {
  -name: String
  -inhabitants: Integer
}

class Attraction {
  -name: String
  -address: String
}

class GuidedTour {
  -duration: Integer
  -maxVisitors: Integer = 20
  -discountAmount: Double
}

class Visitor {
  -name: String
}

class Guide {
  -name: String
}

City "1" *-- "0..*" Attraction : has

Attraction "1" *-- "0..*" GuidedTour : offers

GuidedTour "1" --> "1" Guide : requires

GuidedTour "1" --> "0..*" Visitor : includes

Visitor "0..*" --> "0..*" GuidedTour : participates in (with discount)
@enduml

### Explanation of the Diagram:
- **`City`** has a name and a number of inhabitants.
- **`Attraction`** has a name and an address.
- **`GuidedTour`** has a duration, maximum of 20 visitors, and a discount amount for certain visitors.
- **`Visitor`** and **`Guide`** are both people with names.
- A city can have multiple attractions.
- An attraction can offer multiple guided tours.
- Each guided tour is led by one guide.
- A guided tour can include multiple visitors.
- Visitors may be granted discounts for specific guided tours.

